The paper deals with compressed sensing and sparse signal recovery, which are topics commonly studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of the restricted isometry constant (RIC) and the focus on iterative algorithms such as OMP and gOMP suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the mention of "multi-matching pursuit" in the abstract suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category, which often deals with signal processing and analysis.
